; speakers/readers.<br>&gt; <br>&gt; Indexes also has the disadvantage of being a verb as well as a plural noun.<br></p><p>That thought did cross my mind, but I think the potential for verb/noun confusion seems pretty well handled by context. As a verb, &quot;index&quot; is most commonly transitive, so I&#39;d expect &#39;foo.indexes&#39; to be a property whose value produces indexes, and &#39;foo.indexes(...)&#39;, if it existed, to be some kind of predicate method.<br></p><p>-Joe<br></p></div></li></ul></li></ul></div>    </main>
